Job Description:
Summary of position
Our Client is the Cambodian subsidiary of an international company producing TV shows and running resorts dedicated to tourism and TV production. The Maintenance Manager will be responsible for managing the whole engineering department at the resort.

Main Duties and responsibilities
•	Manage the maintenance and repairs of the interior and exterior of buildings, hotel rooms and contents;
•	Develop and implement a preventive maintenance program incorporating regular, scheduled checks of all buildings and equipment;
•	Conduct maintenance, repair and maintain all equipment include, electrical, plumbing, lighting, laundry, fridges, air conditioners, water system and pump, ice machines, washers, dryers, irons, electrical components, switch gears, panels, motor controls, and boilers etc;
•	Ensure all pathways, buildings and walls are clean and the resort surrounds are clean and tidy;
•	Test and examine the safety systems to ensure they are 100% operational at all times. Monitors utility consumption to determine the effectiveness of current systems;
•	Ensure grounds staff are performing their duties to the highest level;
•	Ensure grounds staff have the necessary tools and supplies to perform their duties;
•	Responsible for determining the security requirements necessary to ensure that hotel property, employees, and guests are protected against theft, crime, working with the resort and sailing clubs security guards;
•	Other tasks assigned by the manager.

Reporting
•	To the Director

Job Requirement:
•	Bachelor’s degree in engineering or equivalent;
•	Minimum 7 years-experience in engineering maintenance in hospitality sector or relevant experience;
•	Very good knowledge of hotel maintenances;
•	Good leadership and management skills;
•	Strong at organization skills, able to work independentlyand part of team;
•	Must be patient, self-motivated and team building capabilities;
•	Proficiency in English.

