Job Description:
Summary of position

Our client is a manufacturer, producing most of the collection, essentially textile, in its several factories in Asia. The Human Resources/CSR Manager will be in charge of implementation and follow-up of HR policy, processes and tools to maximize the operational effectiveness and people strategies.

Main Duties and responsibilities
•	Implement HR guidelines, policies and procedures and manage human potential of operations in compliance with corporate standards and business issues;
•	According to the company standards, ensure recruitment/selection and mobility processes;
•	Monitor employees’ integration, training and performance appraisal review system;
•	Ensure compliance and auditing procedure with local labor law and health & safety regulations;
•	Administer employees file and attendance, timework,insurance, immigration issue and work permit application process;
•	Establish the talent management;
•	Implement the Compensation & Benefits policy and salary grids; analyze data to determine changes and trends in market compensation;
•	Liaise with Finance Manager for payroll and benefits;
•	Ensure Human Resources Information Systems data is accurately maintained;
•	Produce report in Chinese & English to head quarter.

Reporting
•	Report to the Factory Manager

Job Requirement:
•	Master Degree in Human Resources Management or equivalent;
•	Minimum 10 years experience in HR management position (factory experience preferred);
•	Fluent in Chinese and English and must be a Khmer native;
•	Experience in maintaining highest level of standards in a multicultural and international company;
•	Used to work under pressure and reach objectives;
•	Good understanding of CSR and familiar with GMAC, UNION, etc. 
•	Initiative, team-spirit, strong in compliance and auditing;
•	Excellent organizational skills and creating new strategies in HR, attention to details;
•	Good and positive attitude.

